\fs24
\pard\b MediConnect \u8212? Project Documentation\b0\par
\pard Version: March 2026\par
\pard\par

\pard\b 1) Project overview\b0\par
\pard MediConnect is a Flask-based Online Hospital Platform with:\par
\pard - Role-based access (User / Doctor / Admin)\par
\pard - Doctor consultation request and WebRTC video call rooms\par
\pard - AI Chatbot (Gemini) with chat history storage\par
\pard - Medical store listing + cart page (UI)\par
\pard - Real-time notifications using Socket.IO\par
\pard\par

\pard\b 2) Tech stack\b0\par
\pard - Backend: Python + Flask\par
\pard - Database: SQLite via Flask-SQLAlchemy\par
\pard - Auth: Flask-Login\par
\pard - Password hashing: Flask-Bcrypt\par
\pard - Real-time: Flask-SocketIO (Windows-friendly threading async mode)\par
\pard - Frontend: Jinja2 templates + static CSS/JS\par
\pard - Video: WebRTC (browser) + Socket.IO signaling\par
\pard - Chatbot: Google Gemini API (\f1 google-generativeai\f0)\par
\pard\par

\pard\b 3) Repository / folder structure\b0\par
\pard\f1
mediconnect/\par
  app.py\par
  config.py\par
  extensions.py\par
  requirements.txt\par
  models/\par
    user.py\par
    doctor.py\par
    appointment.py\par
    chat.py\par
    medical_store.py\par
  routes/\par
    __init__.py\par
    auth.py\par
    user.py\par
    doctor.py\par
    admin.py\par
    chatbot.py\par
    store.py\par
    video.py\par
  templates/\par
    base.html\par
    index.html\par
    auth/\par
    user/\par
    doctor/\par
    admin/\par
    store/\par
    chatbot/\par
  static/\par
    css/\par
    js/\par
\f0\par

\pard\b 4) How the app boots (startup sequence)\b0\par
\pard - \f1 app.py\f0 creates the Flask app and loads configuration from \f1 config.py\f0.\par
\pard - Initializes extensions: SQLAlchemy, LoginManager, Socket.IO, Bcrypt.\par
\pard - Registers all blueprints (auth, user, doctor, admin, chatbot, store, video).\par
\pard - Creates all DB tables on first run (\f1 db.create_all()\f0).\par
\pard - Seeds a default admin user if missing:\par
\pard   Email: \f1 admin@mediconnect.com\f0 / Password: \f1 admin123\f0\par
\pard\par

\pard\b 5) Roles and permissions\b0\par
\pard Access control is enforced using \f1 routes/role_required()\f0 (wraps Flask-Login).\par
\pard - User: patient dashboard, consult, request call, join own rooms, store, chatbot\par
\pard - Doctor: doctor dashboard, toggle availability, accept/decline, join assigned rooms, store, chatbot\par
\pard - Admin: admin dashboard, register doctors, approve doctors, add medicines, join any room\par
\pard\par

\pard\b 6) Database schema (models)\b0\par
\pard\f1
users\par
  id (PK)\par
  name\par
  email (unique)\par
  password_hash\par
  role = user|doctor|admin\par
\par
doctors\par
  id (PK)\par
  user_id (FK users.id, unique)\par
  specialization\par
  is_available (bool)\par
  is_approved (bool)\par
\par
appointments\par
  id (PK)\par
  user_id (FK users.id)\par
  doctor_id (FK doctors.id)\par
  status = pending|active|done|declined\par
  room_id (unique)\par
  created_at\par
\par
chat_history\par
  id (PK)\par
  user_id (FK users.id)\par
  message\par
  response\par
  timestamp\par
\par
medicines\par
  id (PK)\par
  name\par
  description\par
  price\par
  stock\par
  image_url\par
\f0\par

\pard\b 7) HTTP routes (high-level)\b0\par
\pard\b1 Auth (routes/auth.py)\b0\par
\pard - \f1 GET /login\f0, \f1 POST /login\f0\par
\pard - \f1 GET /signup\f0, \f1 POST /signup\f0\par
\pard - \f1 GET /logout\f0\par
\pard\par
\pard\b1 User (routes/user.py, prefix /user)\b0\par
\pard - \f1 GET /user/dashboard\f0\par
\pard - \f1 GET /user/consult\f0\par
\pard - \f1 POST /user/request-call/<doctor_id>\f0\par
\pard\par
\pard\b1 Doctor (routes/doctor.py, prefix /doctor)\b0\par
\pard - \f1 GET /doctor/dashboard\f0\par
\pard - \f1 POST /doctor/toggle-availability\f0\par
\pard - \f1 POST /doctor/accept/<appointment_id>\f0\par
\pard - \f1 POST /doctor/decline/<appointment_id>\f0\par
\pard\par
\pard\b1 Admin (routes/admin.py, prefix /admin)\b0\par
\pard - \f1 GET /admin/dashboard\f0\par
\pard - \f1 GET|POST /admin/register-doctor\f0\par
\pard - \f1 POST /admin/approve-doctor/<doctor_id>\f0\par
\pard - \f1 POST /admin/medicine/add\f0\par
\pard\par
\pard\b1 Chatbot (routes/chatbot.py, prefix /chat)\b0\par
\pard - \f1 GET /chat/\f0 (chat page)\par
\pard - \f1 POST /chat/ask\f0 (JSON API)\par
\pard\par
\pard\b1 Store (routes/store.py, prefix /store)\b0\par
\pard - \f1 GET /store/\f0\par
\pard - \f1 GET /store/cart\f0\par
\pard\par
\pard\b1 Video (routes/video.py, prefix /video)\b0\par
\pard - \f1 GET /video/room/<room_id>\f0 (role + ownership check)\par
\pard\par

\pard\b 8) Real-time events (Socket.IO)\b0\par
\pard Two namespaces are used:\par
\pard\b1 A) /notifications\b0\par
\pard - \f1 join_user { user_id }\f0  \u8594? room \f1 user:<id>\f0\par
\pard - \f1 join_doctor { doctor_id }\f0 \u8594? room \f1 doctor:<id>\f0\par
\pard - Server emits:\par
\pard   \f1 call_request\f0 \u8594? to doctor room when user requests consultation\par
\pard   \f1 call_accepted\f0 \u8594? to user room when doctor accepts\par
\pard   \f1 call_declined\f0 \u8594? to user room when doctor declines\par
\pard\par
\pard\b1 B) /video (WebRTC signaling)\b0\par
\pard - \f1 join_room { room }\f0\par
\pard - \f1 leave_room { room }\f0\par
\pard - \f1 offer { room, offer }\f0\par
\pard - \f1 answer { room, answer }\f0\par
\pard - \f1 ice-candidate { room, candidate }\f0\par
\pard - \f1 end_call { room }\f0\par
\pard\par

\pard\b 9) Flowcharts (ASCII)\b0\par
\pard The diagrams below are designed to be copy/paste friendly.\par
\pard\par

\pard\b1 9.1 Login / Signup flow\b0\par
\pard\f1
  +---------+        +--------------------+\par
  |  User   |        |  MediConnect (Web) |\par
  +----+----+        +----------+---------+\par
       |                        |\par
       |  GET /login            |\par
       +----------------------->|\par
       |  POST /login (email,pw)|\par
       +----------------------->|\par
       |                        | validate user + role\par
       |                        | set session (Flask-Login)\par
       |  redirect to dashboard |\par
       <-----------------------+\par
\f0\par
\pard\par

\pard\b1 9.2 Consult \u8594? Appointment \u8594? Video Call flow (core)\b0\par
\pard\f1
  Patient                         Server                          Doctor\par
  -------                         ------                          ------\par
  /user/consult\par
     |  POST /user/request-call/<doctor_id>\par
     +--------------------------->|\par
     |                            | create Appointment(status=pending, room_id)\par
     |                            | emit call_request to room doctor:<id> (/notifications)\par
     |                            +--------------------------------------------->|\par
     |                            |                                             | Doctor dashboard reload / shows pending\par
     |                            |  POST /doctor/accept/<appointment_id>\par
     |                            |<---------------------------------------------+\par
     |                            | set Appointment(status=active)\par
     |                            | emit call_accepted to room user:<id> (/notifications)\par
     |  auto redirect /video/room/<room_id>\par
     +<---------------------------+\par
     |                                                              redirect /video/room/<room_id>\par
     |                                                              <-----------------------------+\par
     |  WebRTC in browser: getUserMedia + negotiate via /video namespace\par
     +----------------------- (Socket.IO offer/answer/ICE) ------------------------>\par
\f0\par
\pard\par

\pard\b1 9.3 Video Room (WebRTC signaling)\b0\par
\pard\f1
  Browser A                     Socket.IO Server                     Browser B\par
  ---------                     ---------------                     ---------\par
  join_room(room_id)  ------->  join_room(room_id)\par
  createOffer + setLocalDesc\par
  offer(room_id, SDP) ------->  broadcast offer to room (excluding self) ----->\par
                                                                  setRemoteDesc\par
                                                                  createAnswer + setLocalDesc\par
  answer(room_id, SDP) <-----  broadcast answer to room  <---------------------\par
  ICE candidates (both sides) \par
  ice-candidate  <---------->  broadcast to room  <-------------------------->\par
\f0\par
\pard\par

\pard\b1 9.4 Chatbot flow (Gemini)\b0\par
\pard\f1
  User -> POST /chat/ask {message}\par
           |\par
           | if GEMINI_API_KEY missing: return friendly message\par
           | else: call Gemini model, return reply\par
           | store (user_id, message, response) in chat_history\par
           v\par
        JSON {reply}\par
\f0\par
\pard\par

\pard\b1 9.5 Admin flow: register + approve doctor\b0\par
\pard\f1
  Admin -> GET /admin/register-doctor\par
       -> POST /admin/register-doctor (name,email,password,specialization)\par
            creates User(role=doctor) + Doctor(is_approved=false)\par
       -> POST /admin/approve-doctor/<doctor_id>\par
            sets Doctor.is_approved=true\par
\f0\par
\pard\par

\pard\b 10) Configuration (.env)\b0\par
\pard Required:\par
\pard - \f1 SECRET_KEY\f0\par
\pard Optional:\par
\pard - \f1 GEMINI_API_KEY\f0 (enables chatbot)\par
\pard - \f1 TURN_URL, TURN_USERNAME, TURN_PASSWORD\f0 (improves video call connectivity)\par
\pard\par

\pard\b 11) Local run (Windows) and verification\b0\par
\pard Start:\par
\pard\li360\f1 .\run.ps1\f0\par
\pard\li0
\pard Verify in browser:\par
\pard - \f1 http://localhost:5000\f0 loads landing page\par
\pard - Login at \f1 /login\f0\par
\pard\par
\pard Video call test:\par
\pard - Use two browser sessions (Chrome normal + Incognito)\par
\pard - Login as patient in one, doctor in the other\par
\pard - Patient requests call; doctor accepts; both click Start\par
\pard\par

\pard\b 12) Production notes (important)\b0\par
\pard - Use HTTPS in real deployments (camera/mic permissions).\par
\pard - Ensure reverse proxy supports WebSocket upgrades for Socket.IO.\par
\pard - Add TURN for best reliability across NAT/firewalls.\par
\pard - Replace dev server with a production deployment approach.\par
\pard\par

